x4freetext: An external beam of 1.37 GeV a-particles
Enriched targets of the following four calcium
and 48Ca (67.1 %). The targets consisted of strips
6 mm wide and had thcknesses of about 200 mg/cm2.
telescope at 18 degr. for intensity beam monitoring
incident alpha-particles was determined by measurements
uncertainty of normalization which is not
included in the error bars shown in the figures.
The errors given are due to statistics,
subtraction of the background, subtraction of the
contribution contamining isotopes in the target, and
the correction for the finite angular resolution.
